This paper is about action recognition using deep learning algorithms, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces a new method for pooling CNN features using kernel linearization, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep neural networks, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also involves the use of higher-order correlations, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
